commit.message:
fix references with underscores

When a reference points to a variable in the same subsection,
the section number shall not be part of the reference.
If the variable name contains an underscore,
this was not the case up to now, for the LaTeX version.
Change version to 1.6.7.dev
Push version to 1.6.7
Mention some more changes before release.

FormatParagraph improve handling of too long lines

When a chunk of text without space is longer than the width of the
result, it could happen that a new line was started in inappropriate
places and that some escape sequences got lost. This is fixed here.

Thanks to Thomas Breuer for an example.
Generate nice quotation marks in (X)HTML, too

Fix problem with "--" in LaTeX/PDF version

LaTeX sometimes interprets "--" in typewriter font (e.g., coming
from <C>, <K> and other GAPDoc elements) as ligature for 'endash'
and then displays it as single dash "-".

This is now avoided by handling "-" as special character like "_",
"{", "}" and so on.

Fix a problem with Verbatim commandchars

All characters appearing in the used commands must also be avoided as
`commandchars`.

Problem noticed and fix proposed by Fabian Zickgraf.
avoid search entries in `manual.six` starting with `.`

Change back https to http in DOCTYPE and xmlns.

The corresponding http URLs redirect to their https counterparts.
But in DOCTYPE and XML namespace declarations the http version is used
as identifier and should not be changed.
Avoid overfull line in PDF-version.

Updating various URL's

Often this is just a change from `http` to `https`. But also changed
some outdated ones.
Update RWTH links to https
Drop reference to tetex (support ended 2006)
Update GAP links and a few more to https
Fix links to archives.
Remove leftover references to SingleHTTPRequest
Version change to .dev after 1.6.6 release
Small update.
Search for GAP prompts also in <Listing> elements
Adjust version and date for 1.6.6 release.

Avoid InstallValue for non-plain objects

InstallValue is one of a tiny handful of places calling the GAP kernel
function CLONE_OBJ. This function is rather dangerous, e.g. for *types* it is
not really well-defined, see https://github.com/gap-system/gap/issues/1637.
While I am not aware of any ill-effects of the usage here, I think it is best
to avoid it (and perhaps we can at some point even phase out support for
`InstallValue` used on non-plain objects)
Avoid double parentheses.

Adjustment of commit 07078d9 for manual.six

Reintroduce using the attribute 'Subkey' for <Index> as subkey if
not given as element.

Use warning instead of error

We avoid errors when XML validation does not work because of missing IO
package or missing external command 'xmllint'.
Mention last change.

Avoid some unnecessary processing

This accelerates the construction of the LaTeX source.

(Max Horn noticed warnings which were issued during the extra
processing when building the manual for the anupq package.)

Add script for test files from manual examples

Creates two versions, without and with <Log> elements.
Mention recent changes

Adjust labeling of examples in documentation

Changed the labelling of some examples by <Example>, <Log> or
<Listing> elements.

Made some examples run successfully outside the GAPDoc directory.
